premise_source_doc_sentence: Raymond G. Gosling  (  15 July 1926 -- 18 May 2015  )  was a British scientist who deduced the structure of DNA with Maurice Wilkins and Rosalind Franklin at King 's College , London .

Photograph 51 is the nickname given to an X-ray diffraction image of DNA taken by Raymond Gosling in May 1952 , working as a PhD student under the supervision of Rosalind Franklin , at King 's College London in Sir John Randall 's group .
The first was authored by Francis Crick and James Watson , and the third by Rosalind Franklin and Raymond Gosling .

Photo 51 became a crucial data source that led to the development of the DNA model and confirmed the prior postulated double helical structure of DNA , which were presented in the articles in the Nature journal by Raymond Gosling .

As historians of science have re-examined the period during which this image was obtained , considerable controversy has arisen over both the significance of the contribution of this image to the work of Watson and Crick , as well as the methods by which they obtained the image .
